definitions.definition: Equally distant from one another at all points.
examples: The horizontal lines on my notebook paper are parallel .

definitions.definition: Having the same overall direction ; the comparison is indicated with "to".
examples: The two railway lines are parallel .

labels: said of a pair of lines
definitions.label_groups: hyperbolic geometry , said of a pair of lines

definitions.definition: Involving the processing of multiple tasks at the same time.

examples: the parallel lives of two citizens

definitions.definition: Coexisting but normally not interacting with the regular reality.
definitions.label_groups: science fiction , of realities, dimensions, timelines, etc.

main_definition: Equally distant from one another at all points.
secondary_definitions: Having the same overall direction ; the comparison is indicated with "to".
( hyperbolic geometry , said of a pair of lines ) Either not intersecting , or coinciding .
( computing ) Involving the processing of multiple tasks at the same time.
( science fiction , of realities, dimensions, timelines, etc. ) Coexisting but normally not interacting with the regular reality.
